{% set warningCode %}<p><strong>Warning:</strong> This action cannot be undone.</p>
<p><strong>Do not</strong> share your password with anyone.</p>{% endset %}

{% set nestedCode %}<p><strong>This is important.
  <strong>This is very important.</strong>
</strong></p>{% endset %}

{% set strongVsBCode %}<!-- strong: importance / urgency -->
<p><strong>Warning:</strong> This action is destructive.</p>

<!-- b: attention without importance -->
<p>Try the <b>Classic Burger</b> — our most popular item.</p>{% endset %}

{% set boldInCodeCode %}<pre><code>const result = <strong>calculateTotal</strong>(items);</code></pre>{% endset %}

{% set strongCssCode %}strong, b {
  font-weight: 600;
  font-synthesis: none;     /* prevent faux bold */
  font-optical-sizing: auto;
}

/* Combined bold + italic */
:where(strong em, em strong) {
  font-weight: 600;
  font-style: italic;
  font-synthesis: none;
}

/* Bold in code — highlight background */
:where(code, pre) :where(b, strong) {
  background-color: oklch(from var(--color-interactive) l c h / 0.12);
  border-radius: var(--radius-s);
  padding-inline: var(--size-2xs);
}{% endset %}

<section>
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;strong&gt;</code> element indicates strong importance, seriousness, or urgency. Screen readers may announce it with a change in voice. VB styles it with <code>font-weight: 600</code>, <code>font-synthesis: none</code> (prevents faux bold), and <code>font-optical-sizing: auto</code> for variable fonts.</p>
    <p>Inside <code>&lt;code&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;pre&gt;</code>, strong gets a subtle highlight background instead of relying on weight alone.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>When to Use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Warnings:</strong> "Warning: This action cannot be undone"</li>
      <li><strong>Urgency:</strong> "Do not share your password"</li>
      <li><strong>Important labels:</strong> "Important:", "Note:", "Critical:"</li>
      <li><strong>Key facts:</strong> The most important sentence in a paragraph</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>When NOT to Use</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>To draw attention without importance &mdash; use <a href="/docs/elements/native/b/"><code>&lt;b&gt;</code></a></li>
      <li>For stress emphasis that changes meaning &mdash; use <a href="/docs/elements/native/em/"><code>&lt;em&gt;</code></a></li>
      <li>For headings &mdash; use <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code>&ndash;<code>&lt;h6&gt;</code></li>
      <li>Purely for visual styling &mdash; use CSS <code>font-weight</code></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

