  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Some screen readers announce <code>&lt;strong&gt;</code> with a change in voice tone</li>
      <li>This distinguishes it from <code>&lt;b&gt;</code> which is not announced differently</li>
      <li>Nesting <code>&lt;strong&gt;</code> increases the degree of importance semantically</li>
      <li>Do not use strong for every bold word &mdash; overuse dilutes the signal</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

